Jaime Cardriche https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Jaime_Cardriche 0 Jaime Cardriche (March 20, 1968 – July 28, 2000) was an American actor best known for his role as Tim on Malcolm Eddie. Cardriche grew up in Cerritos, California and attended Oklahoma State University where he played both football and basketball. He appeared primarily in sitcoms such as Family Matters, The Fresh Prince of Bel-Air, A Different World, Malcolm Eddie, Who's the Boss?, The Wayans Bros., and Hangin' with Mr. Cooper". He was also a professional wrestler, the Harlem Warlord. His last appearance as an actor was in the episode "A Simple Plan" on the sitcom The Parkers. Cardriche died on July 28, 2000 from complications during gall bladder surgery. He was 32 years old.
